

Problem 222

19 December 2008


What is the length of the shortest pipe, of internal radius 50mm, that can
fully contain 21 balls of radii 30mm, 31mm, ..., 50mm?

Give your answer in micrometres (10^-6 m) rounded to the nearest integer.




                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                           
